User Levels, different interception strategies can be configured for users of different levels. Optional values: 
0: Lowest level users, typically including newly registered, completely inactive, or users with a level of 0;
1: Lower level users, typically including low active or low-level users;
2: Medium level users, typically including users with certain activity or medium-level users;
3: Higher level users, typically including highly active or high-level users;
4: Highest level users, typically including paying users, VIP users, etc.

The channel mode for recording on Agora, with the following values:
0: Communication (default), which is the common 1-to-1 private chat or group chat, where any user in the channel can speak freely;
1: Live broadcasting, with two types of user roles: broadcaster and audience.

